subsection.text:

Section 303(l) of the Social Security Act (
  42 U.S.C. 503(l)
) is amended to read as follows:


Section 303(a)(1) of the Social Security Act (
  42 U.S.C. 503(a)(1)
) shall not be construed in such a manner as to apply the merit staffing requirements in section 900.603 of title 5, Code of Federal Regulations, as in effect on October 1, 2011, to the implementation of section 303(l) of such Act (as amended by subsection (a)).
